<br>
ezBoard also has the advantage of hosting most of the EQ forums that exist -- for servers, for guilds, and for classes.  As a user, it's very conventient to have most of the discussions I visit be handled by one login.<br>
<br>
If this board moves to another system, someone *still* has to pick up the cost of bandwidth or hosting.  The cost is *still* going to be significant, as Ron has said.  So we all need to be trying to figure out how get the right $$$ to keep this community going.<br>
<br>
To understand how we can *reduce* the $ involved, it's important to know how the cost is calculated.  Admins, please correct me if I'm wrong on any of this - It's what I grok'd from the discussions that went on at The Druid's Grove when the last renewal came up.<br>
<br>
First of all, the cost that ezBoard lists will flunctuate based on recent &quot;usage&quot;.  I believe the usage numbers are based on the last 60 days, but I'm not sure on the exact timetable.  Reducing our usage between now and renewal time is the only way to reduce the cost to the community.<br>
<br>
So what is &quot;usage&quot; exactly?  Let's see if I can remember - Each time a non-ezSupporter opens the board, a forum, or a topic, it counts as a hit, right?  Someone mentioned killing graphical sigs to help, but I don't think it will since they are just included in the page hit.  I could be wrong on this though.<br>
<br>
One of the challenges that the board faces is that usage always increases when there are long patches, big changes, and especially expansions.  Unfortunately, we have all three coming between now and the time our renewal is due.  Chalk it up to bad timing - Not much we can do about that one.  Just know that it's possible that it will cost more to renew in a month than less.  *Unless* we can reduce usage even facing the expansion.<br>
<br>
How can you help?<br>
<br>
First, ezSupporters don't count against the boards usage costs.  If you use multiple ezBoards, then please consider signing up for the ezSupporter option - For $12 a year, it means that the boards you visit don't incur any costs on your behalf.<br>
<br>
If you only visit this board, and aren't already an ezSupporter, consider donating for the board's gold renewal.  Of course, as someone above mentioned, wait until Ronaldor makes a move or no-move decision first.<br>
<br>
When the druid board was up for renewal, I noticed something interesting - There are advertising sponsors who will donate a portion of your purchase to the board's renewal.  I encourage everyone to look through these options when the renewal notice goes up on the board.  One example was Netflix, who I was thinking about signing up for anyway - If you signed up, the board got $10.  Look to see if there is something you would be interested there - It could help out the community at the same time.<br>
<br>
Finally, a request - If you don't plan on becoming an ezSupporter or donating to the gold costs of this board, then the best thing you can do to help for the next couple of months is to just stay away - Seriously.  It's *your* visits that will determine the final cost of the Gold renewal.<br>
<br>
The druid board admins even went so far as to lock many of the forums in the final month before the renewal was due.  Only ezSupporters and those who donated were allowed in to the forums such as Quests and Equipment.  While angering some of those who hadn't paid, it did have the effect of reducing the usage numbers drastically.<br>
<br>
Remember, regardless of where this community resides, it's going to cost money.  Bandwidth costs are high, and ezBoard has the ability to offer both bandwidth and admin of a decent board system cheaper than many others simply due to economies of scale.  $800-1000 for 6 months may seem like a lot, but it's not when you look at the costs of a dedicated T1 or higher that this board would require otherwise.<br>
<br>
