<br>
Graphics (on EZBoard at least) do not count towards bandwith.  The bandwith used will be on the server that the pic is linked from.  For that matter, EZBoard photo-hosting is dead at the moment (at least I THINK it still is).  They have had no host for almost a year now...but that would not be bandwith from THIS vboard anyway (just from the EZBoard that the pic was hosted ON).<br>
<br>
What's really weird is that HITS (even from CSC Admin) in the CONTROL center counts towards bandwith (eyeroll). <p><center><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaSig.gif"><br><br><b><font face="garamond" size=3><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543802">My Magelo Profile</a></center><font size=0 font face=garamond font color=black></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/22/03 6:33:38 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 5:49:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8523.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mag tower gold status</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Remember, regardless of where this community resides, it's going to cost money. Bandwidth costs are high, and ezBoard has the ability to offer both bandwidth and admin of a decent board system cheaper than many others simply due to economies of scale. $800-1000 for 6 months may seem like a lot, but it's not when you look at the costs of a dedicated T1 or higher that this board would require otherwise.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Um, no offense, but I've found that ezboard is waaay higher than just about any other solution in existence.  And that includes other hosted forums, as well as do it yourself solutions.<br>
<br>
Bandwidth is not costly ... bandwidth has never been cheaper at this point, whether you're buying fractional T1's or OC3 backbones.<br>
<br>
Hosting is not costly ... there are loads of hosted companies out there desperately trying to get customers right now so that they can stave off bankruptcy.  Costs have never been lower.<br>
<br>
Forum software is not costly ... There are many solutions out there ranging from free to inexpensive.  It all depends on the feature set that you're interested in.<br>
<br>
The point is that ezboard had a good business model: they offered free forums at a critical juncture in the mmorpg industry.  Now, once those forums are established and running, they're making their profit.  More power to them.  I hope they keep it up, since I've made over $8k in contract work moving people off of them.<br>
<br>
But thinking that because you're paying a premium price that you're getting a premium service is simply naive. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A> at: 1/22/03 5:50:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=legolys>Legolys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 6:39:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8523.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mag tower gold status</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Bandwidth is not costly ... bandwidth has never been cheaper at this point, whether you're buying fractional T1's or OC3 backbones.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's still going to be the most expensive component of hosting a board like this.  I'm no expert on pricing, but the $100-150 a month ezBoard is asking seems reasonable to me when it includes bandwidth *and* hosting and admin.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Hosting is not costly ... there are loads of hosted companies out there desperately trying to get customers right now so that they can stave off bankruptcy. Costs have never been lower.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree that hosting is not costly.  But do I really want to give my money to a company that is trying to &quot;stave off bankruptcy&quot;?  These guys are more than willing to convert all the ezBoard postings *to* their system today, but what happens when they go bankrupt (or, more commonly, just move on to more profitable pastures)?<br>
<br>
I love cheap hosting, don't get me wrong - It's perfect for my personal web site.  But is that where we want to put a community of several thousand?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Forum software is not costly ... There are many solutions out there ranging from free to inexpensive. It all depends on the feature set that you're interested in.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Never said forum software was expensive.  The advantage that ezBoard has over &quot;forum software&quot; is that ezBoard takes care of much of the admin process, freeing up the time of Ronaldor and others.  Managing the updates, database, bugs, and whatever that come with software takes time - A lot of it.  If Ronaldor, or someone else has the time and energy to put into complete admin of a board system, then fantastic.  But it's not right for us to ask him to do this for the community.  It's more fair for us to poney up the money to take this pressure off of him.<br>
<br>
- Lego <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 6:56:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8523.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mag tower gold status</span><hr size=1> $100-150 / month for bandwidth?  LOL, it's waaay more than that.<br>
<br>
The last board I moved went to a provider that provided hosting, diskspace, bandwidth and admin for $9.99 per month.  I provided phpBB for free, moved their forums over, and bought another 1Gb of diskspace for a reasonable amount.<br>
<br>
Net savings: $883 per quarter to &lt;$100.<br>
<br>
All hosting companies provide bandwidth as part of their service.  The price depends on the company.  The above is the cheapest I'd found as of September, 2002.  The board previous to that had some specific requirements on hosting, so we went with a more expensive provider that pushed the price up to over $200 per quarter.<br>
<br>
Bandwidth is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>cheap</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<br>
My point is that the current turmoil in the computer industry means that hosting companies are begging for customers.  They're offering free toasters with every account.  If one goes out of business that doesn't mean their servers go down... usually they're bought by another hosting company.<br>
<br>
Even if they do go down, so what?  You move to another.  Big deal: if you get warning, downtime is nonexistent.  <br>
<br>
If you don't, you can move a forum and its data (assuming you go with something like phpBB which is fairly standard in setup and admin) in less than 2 hours.  Point the DNS servers to the new host, and you're back in business fast.<br>
<br>
As for the massive &quot;admin costs&quot; associated with forum software... never noticed it myself.  Forum software is pretty good nowadays.  The single biggest thing that I do is handling botched account requests ... but that's because I don't moderate.  Most of the work associated with forums comes from moderation.<br>
<br>
Which you have with ezboard as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ronaldorvladimir>Ronaldor Vladimir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_8ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 945<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 3:39:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8523.topic&index=32>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://magecompendium.zombie-jesus.com/domus/Images/Guild_Logo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mag tower gold status</span><hr size=1> everyone is missing my point, my main concern is raising the money to pay for the bandwidth/hosting (i cannot afford to pay for the bandwidth), if the money isnt raised on most other solutions the board would be shut down till the bills were paid, on ezboard if it isnt raised we just have to put up with adverts for a bit till we do, and with a large number of people now using persoanl csc thats not to much of a problem. <p><font face="Verdana" size="1">
